&lt;p id=&quot;isPasted&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHO WE ARE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Headquartered in Grand Rapids, Michigan since 1955, Lumbermen’s operates in Michigan, Ohio, Indiana, Kentucky, and Minnesota. A leading distributor and manufacturer, we are driven by the goal to be first choice for our employee owners, customers, and suppliers. Lumbermen’s is 100% employee-owned and committed to investing in rewarding relationships and doing the right thing in every interaction.&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POSITION SUMMARY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Located at our Byron Center, MI location, the position of CNC Operator is in place for the purpose of installing glass and door bottoms, packaging, and completing other value-add processes to doors being cut by the CNC. The associate will be responsible for the timeliness, accuracy, and completion of these daily operations. &amp;nbsp;Installing glass and other door components.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring the proper quality, accuracy and timeliness of the prepping of all doors for specials, line, and finish.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Properly staging all doors for production or shipping.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining the organization, maintenance, and cleanliness of the CNC area, assigned by the CNC Supervisor&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with shipping to pull individual components for customer orders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring that all production areas are properly supplied for the day’s work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performing other tasks as assigned by the CNC Supervisor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position offers a $300 annual clothing allowance for uniform, protective footwear, and PPE.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;REQUIRED EDUCATION/EXPERIENCE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul type=&quot;disc&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School diploma/GED required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior woodworking would be considered a plus; router, miter saws, table saws&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior CNC operation would be considered a plus, but not required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of exterior doors would be considered a plus, but not required.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;REQUIRED SKILLS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul type=&quot;disc&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently&amp;nbsp;and in a fast-paced environment&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work safely and efficiently at all times&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dependable and reliable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to accurately read orders and stage material to internal customer needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and desire to “do things right the first time”&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PHYSICAL REQUIREMENTS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul type=&quot;disc&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lift up to 75 lb&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to stand for 8-10&amp;nbsp;hours/day&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
