&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHO WE ARE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Headquartered in Grand Rapids, Michigan since 1955, Lumbermen’s operates in Michigan, Ohio, Indiana, Kentucky, and Minnesota. A leading distributor and manufacturer, we are driven by our mission to enrich lives by intentionally caring for all who experience us. &amp;nbsp;We are&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;employee owned&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;relationship powered&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;HOURS: 1st Shift&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU WILL BE DOING:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based out of our Toledo Division, our CDL-A Truck Drivers pick up goods from our suppliers and deliver them to our customers, building and solidifying strong business relationships. They may also transfer goods between our locations. Day-to-day responsibilities include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Living Out Lumbermen’s Culture&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;– Leading in and modeling Lumbermen’s core values while creating an atmosphere where Lumbermen’s is ‘first choice’ of our customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Loading Products&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;– Loading and unloading trailers using tie down straps and operating side curtain trailers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Securing Orders&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;– Properly securing all material loaded on their truck.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staying Compliant&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;– Properly maintaining their Lumbermen’s-supplied CMV ensuring compliance with required mechanical maintenance per DOT regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ensuring Safety&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;– Following all DOT and Company safety regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Teamwork&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;– Building and maintaining strong relationships on behalf of Lumbermen’s with all those they come in contact with, including customers, suppliers, fellow employee owners and patrons on the road.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Lumbermen’s, our business is built on relationships. &amp;nbsp;It’s crucial that the person selected to fill this role is a safety-minded team player who gets energy from contributing to collaborative success.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position offers a $300 annual clothing allowance to offset costs for work apparel, protective footwear, and PPE.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHO WE NEED:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An employee owner&amp;nbsp;who embraces, models, and promotes Lumbermen’s Mission, Vision, and Promise and has:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to effectively work and communicate with fellow employee owners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to handle a variety of tasks at one time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Desire to “do things right the first time.”&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work and drive safely and efficiently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Qualifications/Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School diploma/GED required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CDL Class A license with a clean driving record&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to operate a forklift (trailer loading experience a plus).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to do physical labor including lifting of up to 75lbs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
